# TaskMaster Setup

## Backend Setup

* Create the project folder:

  ```bash
  mkdir TaskMaster
  ```

* Go inside and create backend folder:

  ```bash
  cd TaskMaster
  mkdir Backend
  ```

* Initialize Node.js project:

  ```bash
  cd Backend
  npm init -y
  ```

* Install dependencies:

  ```bash
  npm install express cors
  ```

* Create `server.js` and run the server:

  ```bash
  node server.js
  ```

* Open in browser:

  ```
  http://localhost:5000
  ```

* Update `server.js` with GET, POST, UPDATE, DELETE endpoints

* Restart the server:

  * Press `Ctrl + C` in CMD
  * Run:

    ```bash
    node server.js
    ```

* Test all APIs using Postman / Thunder Client

---

## Frontend Setup

* Stop the backend server:

  * Press `Ctrl + C` in CMD

* Go back to root folder:

  ```bash
  cd ..
  ```

* Create React app:

  ```bash
  npx create-react-app frontend
  ```

* Go to frontend folder:

  ```bash
  cd frontend
  ```

* Start the React server:

  ```bash
  npm start
  ```

* Open in browser:

  ```
  http://localhost:3000
  ```

* Update `src/App.js` and `App.css` to connect frontend with backend (implement all functionalities)


# ⚙️ Additional Setup

## Create `.gitignore`

```bash
touch .gitignore
```

Add:

```
node_modules/
build/
.env
```

